      "content": "Applying hydrogen peroxide can actually damage new tissue and delay healing, while hydrocortisone creams are generally not recommended for infected or open surgical wounds. Since you had a procedure done recently, any signs of redness or discharge should be evaluated by your surgeon to rule out complications like a spreading infection. It is best to call their surgery center for a quick online registration or advice rather than assume it will heal on its own with the wrong products.",
      "source": "target",
